<br>
NOTHING, aside from laziness and the reasons he laid out (to wit, that ranting and trolling isn't really fun unless there are people who are going to be offended) is stopping you from starting your own forum. With your own rules, or lack thereof. As such, your complaint is not especially valid. No one *owes* you the flame wars you consider to be entertainment. <br>
<br>
No one is being oppressed here. <br>
<br>
As for a power trip - come on, do you really think anyone besides an insecure teenager (Which Valquiss hardly strikes me as) would get a power trip from being a *message board moderator*? Give me a break. You really think there's much of a power trip involved in constantly getting whined at by people with too much time on their hands? Sounds like a major annoyance to me and definitely not a job I'd be lining up to volunteer for. And &quot;censorship&quot; definitely doesn't even make it to my top-ten list of 'ultimate highs'.<br>
