eplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=369.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Moderators</span><hr size=1> This is silly.  Yes people have the right to go make their own boards, its free and not very hard to signup for one.  <br>
<br>
This board is moderated:  Live with it.  Just because Joe, George and Sally want to get all bulled up and curse at the monitor while typing about Dick, Andy and Jane being loot whores and board nazis and the dreaded Uberfools, that doesn't mean that its just a part of a message board ya know.<br>
<br>
I didn't foresee this board being la la land or anything where everyone is pollyanna, but I am a reasonably mature adult, I can make a post without cursing, blaming or purposefully infuriating others even when I want to make a point.  If I can do that, other people can too.  See when you grow a bit older, strife and proving your point at all costs (no matter how passionate of a person you are, and trust me I can be pretty passionate about some issues I believe in) isn't always the best way to handle things.<br>
