<br>
On the topic of making your own board or leaving your country.  Even though there is nothing stopping you from emmigrating to other countries (at least in most of the world) convinience is not a factor when it comes to free speach.  I do not know your nationalities but I am an American and I have grown accustomed to it.  I play on Firiona Vie and I want to know what my peers think.  If you are going to take on the responsibility of moderating an &quot;official&quot; Firiona Vie board, then you need to accept the fact that you must cater to and tolerate each and every one of your visitors no matter how &quot;immature&quot; they are or how strong of opinions they have. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utitaisia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Titaisia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/15/02 1:33:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=369.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Moderators</span><hr size=1> Ummm...  Free speech means you have the right to make your message heard through your own means.  It doesn't give you the right to paint your messages on the sides of people's houses.<br>
