Ok well first of all even with the advent of free speech in America and the 5th Amendment, there is no true free speech available.  There are laws pertaining to hate crimes, sexual harrassment laws, inappropriate words and inappropriate visualizations that aren't allowed in mainstream legal America.<br>
<br>
So don't use this American Freedom of Speech to rationalize that its ok to harrassment, condemn, aggravate and instigate others to aggressive reactions.  I tolerate cursing, I have nothing against cursing, I curse myself *egads*, but there is a difference of cursing because you stepped on a rusty nail and cursing to hurt someone.<br>
<br>
Let me tell you something about &quot;catering and tolerate each and every one of the visitors&quot; to this board.  That is nice in print, but with each individual personality and individual likes and dislikes of aaaaallll the people who come here, that is just impossible.  You know the saying &quot;can't please everyone all the time&quot; and you know what?  Thats true.  Its impossible.  If everyone was happy the world sure the heck wouldn't be the way it is now.<br>
<br>
I am American, I was born in america, in fact I'm Native American, my ancestors were in north america long before the Europeans immigrated, that doens't give me the right to making accusatory statements, harrassing statements, tearing someone apart verbally or emotionally because I think they are wrong.<br>
<br>
This board isn't gonna turn into another Jerry Springer Presents. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
